docs.snippet: The N.F.L. may have built a fan-dazzling roadway in Midtown Manhattan called Super Bowl Boulevard, but the big game, and some of the big names, remain west of the Hudson....
docs.lead_paragraph: The N.F.L. may have built a fan-dazzling roadway in Midtown Manhattan called Super Bowl Boulevard, but the big game, and some of the big names, remain west of the Hudson.
docs.abstract: Dan Barry This Land column notes that many of the 2014 Super Bowl pregame activities are being hosted in New York City even though the game itself will be played at MetLife Stadium in East Rutherford, New Jersey; reminds readers to remember that New Jersey, despite being overshadowed by New York, has its own vibrant history and has produced many celebrated public figures.

headline.main: Super Bowl Fans, Do Not Forget: It’s New Jersey
headline.print_headline: Football Fans, Do Not Forget, It’s New Jersey
